HEADWORD: Three-coat
<hw>Three"-coat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>Having or consisting of three coats; -- applied to plastering which
consists of pricking-up, floating, and a finishing coat; or, as called
in the United States, a scratch coat, browning, and finishing
coat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-color</ent>⟦br⟧
